The hit Discovery Channel show will be going off-air after the end of its 14th season, according to Entertainment Weekly . Season 14 is slated to premiere Jan. 3, 2016 at 8 p.m.
Since 2003, Adam Savage, Jamie Hyneman and the gang have tried to debunk scientific urban legends from their filming locations around San Francisco, California -- nearly 3,000 experiments in all .
Savage and Hyneman reportedly knew the end was nigh for years, which allowed them the time to craft out a final goodbye and send the show off with a bang. Like you do.
"It was my greatest fear that 'MythBusters' would just stop and we wouldn't be able to do proper final episodes," Savage told Entertainment Weekly . "So whether it's myths about human behavior or car stories or explosion stories, we tried to find the most awesome example of each category and build on our past history."
That's not the only show to get the ax this year. Take a look at the gallery above for other TV shows that were canceled or ended this year.
